subject: p13475033
Findings: Single portable view of the chest is compared to previous exam from. Dual-lumen right subclavian central line is again seen with tip at the RA-SVC junction. Increased interstitial markings seen throughout the lungs are again noted and suggestive of chronic interstitial disease. Right mid lung opacity has resolved. The cardiomediastinal silhouette is stable as are the osseous and soft tissue structures.
Impression: No acute cardiopulmonary process. Persistent increased interstitial markings in the lungs compatible with chronic interstitial disease. Interval resolution of the right mid lung opacity since prior.
